<subSubSection id="C33A6517FF9E2162DA0BFC17FA2C619F" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9F369CFF9E2162DA0BFC17FA2C619F" blockId="19.[827,1469,855,1361]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801">
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1FFF9E2162DA0BFC17FC1C61FE" authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[828,947,897,921]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Holzapfelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B954EA8EFF9E2162DA0BFC17FC1C61FE" box="[828,947,897,921]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801">Holzapfelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Holz.ap.fe’li.a. N.L. fem. n. 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1FFF9E2162DDDBFC17FACC61FE" authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[1260,1379,897,921]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Holzapfelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B954EA8EFF9E2162DDDBFC17FACC61FE" box="[1260,1379,897,921]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801">Holzapfelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, named after Wilhelm Holzapfel, a microbiologist and taxonomist who made significant contributions to the understanding of the physiology and applications of lactic acid bacteria).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33A6517FF9E2162DA0BFB98FB356745" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9F369CFF9E2162DA0BFB98FB356745" blockId="19.[827,1469,855,1361]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801">
Strains of 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1FFF9E2162DA8BFB98FB966641" authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[956,1081,1038,1062]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Holzapfelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B954EA8EFF9E2162DA8BFB98FB966641" box="[956,1081,1038,1062]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801">Holzapfelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are Gram positive, rod-shaped, catalase negative, homofermentative and aerotolerant. The 
<typeStatus id="549B883EFF9E2162DA0BFBD8FCC46601" box="[828,875,1102,1126]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801">type</typeStatus>
strain of the single species in the genus was isolated from mountain flowers, other strains were identified in bee larvae. 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1FFF9E2162DABDFB1BFBAD66C3" box="[906,1026,1164,1188]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="floricola">
<emphasis id="B954EA8EFF9E2162DABDFB1BFBAD66C3" box="[906,1026,1164,1188]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801">H. floricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows at 15 but not at 37 °C; glucose and fructose are the only carbohydrates that are fermented. The sources of isolation as well as genomic and physiological properties of the organism indicate an insect- and flowerassociated lifestyle of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33A6517FF9E2162DA0BFAAEFAB76737" box="[828,1304,1336,1361]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8B9F369CFF9E2162DA0BFAAEFAB76737" blockId="19.[827,1469,855,1361]" box="[828,1304,1336,1361]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801">
The 
<typeStatus id="549B883EFF9E2162DA5DFAAFFC376736" box="[874,920,1337,1361]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1FFF9E2162DD3DFAAEFB2F6737" authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[1034,1152,1336,1360]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Holzapfelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B954EA8EFF9E2162DD3DFAAEFB2F6737" box="[1034,1152,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801">Holzapfelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1FFF9E2162DDAAFAAFFABD6737" box="[1181,1298,1336,1360]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="floricola">
<emphasis id="B954EA8EFF9E2162DDAAFAAFFABD6737" box="[1181,1298,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="2801">H. floricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
